  <h3 id="action">Adding actions</h3>
  <p>You can add actions to the card's header, they are shown below the heading on small screens and right aligned on bigger screens.</p>
  <p>Card actions cannot be used on clickable cards because the entire card is 1 clickable link.</p>

  {{ designExample({
    group: "components",
    item: "card",
    type: "card-actions"
  }) }}

  <p>Write link text for card actions to tell the user what the card action will do and that it will apply to the entire card. Keep it short and do not add more than 2 to 3 actions in a header.</p>
  <p>Example card actions include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Remove appointment</li>
    <li>Edit appointment</li>
    <li>Update issue</li>
    <li>Approve application</li>
    <li>Cancel order</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Card titles must be unique and help identify what the card contains. Keep titles short and relevant. When card actions are read aloud by screen readers, the card title will be prefixed, making each action link unique.</p>
  <p>If a card action cannot easily be undone or might have serious consequences, consider adding a warning or asking the user for confirmation.</p>

  <h3 class="nhsuk-heading-m">Grouping cards</h3>
  <p>You can group multiple cards to show a collection of related topics or highlight key information and figures.</p>
  <p>If you are grouping cards to create a hub page (sometimes called a landing page) use the <a href="https://service-manual.nhs.uk/design-system/patterns">Hub page pattern</a>.</p>

